description.narrative: In 2021, despite a deterioration of the socio-political and security situation and the incidence of the earthquake, UNICEF strengthened its support for improved access to safe water, hygiene and sanitation in schools and healthcare facilities. A total of 235 schools and 29 healthcare facilities benefited from WASH interventions as a result of UNICEF direct support through its regular WASH programme and response to the COVID-19 pandemic. | Status:Met | As-of Date:16/01/2022
